# AKOS Index Integrity

Use this rule whenever closing a wave inside a multi-wave initiative OR
whenever minting a new canonical CSV under
`docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/Compliance/canonicals/` or its
`dimensions/` subdir. Codifies operator decision **D-IH-86-CD** (operator-
ratified the layered index-integrity discipline as the 11th Quality Fabric
specialty, 2026-05-21). Mechanical companion to
[`INDEX_INTEGRITY_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/INDEX_INTEGRITY_DISCIPLINE.md).

This rule does **not** define the doctrine — that lives in the canonical.
This rule names the mechanical bar that future agents and operators
inherit by default when touching any baseline-index document or canonical
CSV.

## When this rule applies

A sweep is in scope for this rule when **any** of:

- A wave inside a cluster-coordinator initiative closes (I86 precedent;
  future analogous coordinators).
- A new row lands in any canonical CSV under
  `docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/Compliance/canonicals/` or
  `dimensions/`.
- A new `docs/wip/planning/NN-<slug>/` folder is created.
- A new `*_DISCIPLINE.md` specialty canonical is minted under
  `People/canonicals/`.
- The operator explicitly requests a sweep (on_demand cadence).

Waves and commits NOT in scope: chore-only single-commit waves
(typo fixes; link-rot fixes; formatting normalisations) per the
canonical's §4 Exception 1.

## RULE 1 — Run the 8-dimension sweep at every in-scope trigger (binding)

Every in-scope trigger MUST execute the 8-dimension index-freshness sweep
before the wave's UAT verdict line is filled in / before the canonical-CSV
mint commit lands. The sweep output (`reports/index-sweep-<date>.md`
under the parent initiative folder) is a §3 mechanical-evidence row in
the wave's UAT report.

The 8 dimensions are defined in [`INDEX_INTEGRITY_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/INDEX_INTEGRITY_DISCIPLINE.md) §2. Summary:

| # | Dimension code | Index document | Probe heuristic |
|:--|:---|:---|:---|
| 1 | IDX-01-PLANNING-README-INITIATIVE-COUNT | `docs/wip/planning/README.md` | filesystem NN- folder count ↔ INITIATIVE_REGISTRY.csv row count |
| 2 | IDX-02-PRECEDENCE-CSV-COVERAGE | `PRECEDENCE.md` | every CSV under `compliance/canonicals/` + `dimensions/` mentioned |
| 3 | IDX-03-CHANGELOG-WAVE-COVERAGE | `CHANGELOG.md` | last commit's Wave-X marker mentioned in `[Unreleased]` |
| 4 | IDX-04-INITIATIVE-DEPENDENCIES-FRESHNESS | `INITIATIVE_DEPENDENCIES.md` | last-edit within 7d of last registry change |
| 5 | IDX-05-USER-GUIDE-ROLE-PROCESS-COUNTS | `docs/USER_GUIDE.md` HLK Operator Model | role/process counts ↔ canonical CSV counts (~1% wobble) |
| 6 | IDX-06-ARCHITECTURE-HLK-REGISTRY-COVERAGE | `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` HLK Registry | every dimension CSV mentioned |
| 7 | IDX-07-PLANNING-FOLDER-FILESYSTEM-PARITY | `docs/wip/planning/README.md` initiative table | bidirectional FK: folders ↔ README rows |
| 8 | IDX-08-QUALITY-FABRIC-SPECIALTY-COUNT | `HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md` §6 | every `*_DISCIPLINE.md` referenced |

6 dimensions (1-4, 7-8) are **baseline + always fire**. 2 dimensions (5-6)
are **conditional** — they fire only when the relevant source-of-truth has
changed.

## RULE 2 — Findings disposition via inline-ratify 5-option enum (binding)

Every drift/gap/blocked finding from the sweep MUST be dispositioned via
an inline `AskQuestion` gate per [`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc)
+ the paired [`inline-ratify-craft`](../skills/inline-ratify-craft/SKILL.md) skill,
using the 5-option enum codified in `INDEX_INTEGRITY_DISCIPLINE.md` §6:

1. **deterministic-fix-now** (default for drift findings on IDX-01, IDX-02,
   IDX-07, IDX-08).
2. **manual-fix-now** (default for drift findings on IDX-03, IDX-04, IDX-05,
   IDX-06 which require prose judgement).
3. **defer-OPS** (default for low-severity gaps + skip findings).
4. **accept-as-canon** (operator ratifies the drift was deliberate;
   appends contra-precedent + decision row).
5. **escalate-to-blocker-tracker** (cannot be dispositioned in-chat;
   mints `_blockers/<slug>-tracker.md` per [`akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc`](akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc)).

When findings exceed 10, the agent splits the gates into 2 `AskQuestion`
batches (per inline-ratify-craft Principle 5 batching guidance). Time-box
recovery applies only to reversible dispositions per
`akos-inline-ratification.mdc` §"Time-box recovery".

## RULE 3 — Sweep cadence per canonical §4 (binding)

Default cadence: **every wave-close** + **every canonical-CSV mint**.
Exceptions:

- **Chore-only single-commit waves**: exempt entirely.
- **Multi-commit waves**: sweep at wave-close only, not per-commit.
- **Canonical-CSV mints adding < 3 rows to existing CSV**: MAY skip the
  sweep IF the affected dimensions are conditional only (IDX-05, IDX-06)
  AND the operator records the skip in `operator-scratchpad.md`.
- **Pre-commit self-test**: always-on, zero-cost Pydantic fixture
  validation only (`--self-test` mode of the runbook + validator).

No other exemptions. "We're in a hurry" / "we'll do it next wave" are
NOT exemptions per the operator's 2026-05-21 framing.

## RULE 4 — Self-test step wired into pre_commit (binding from D-IH-86-CD)

The runbook `scripts/baseline_index_sweep.py --self-test` AND the
validator `scripts/validate_index_freshness.py --self-test` verify the 8
probe functions exist + return well-formed `IndexFreshnessRow` Pydantic
models. The self-test runs at every `py scripts/verify.py pre_commit`
invocation via [`config/verification-profiles.json`](../../config/verification-profiles.json)
`validate_index_freshness_self_test` step + [`scripts/release-gate.py`](../../scripts/release-gate.py)
`run_index_freshness_self_test`.

The full sweep (without `--self-test`) runs at wave-close + canonical-CSV
mint only — NOT at every pre_commit (which would scan too many files).
The self-test is the always-on circuit-breaker; the full sweep is the
event-triggered gate.

Per D-IH-86-CD INFO → FAIL ramp:

- Wave N (mint): self-test PASS at pre_commit; full sweep runs at Wave N
  close. Validator default mode emits findings at INFO; only `--strict`
  exits non-zero.
- Wave N close: backfill commit closes all baseline-index drift. One
  full sweep emits `drift_count == 0 AND gap_count == 0`.
- Wave O+: validator promoted to FAIL via operator-explicit decision
  (D-IH-86-CD rationale or successor row); `--strict` becomes the default
  mode in pre_commit.

## RULE 5 — Specialty mint contract (binding)

When this rule itself was minted (Wave N P3), it followed the Wave M
INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION precedent — every new Quality Fabric specialty
mint must ship the **same quartet**:

1. Canonical doctrine: `docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/<SPECIALTY>_DISCIPLINE.md`.
2. Pydantic chassis: `akos/hlk_<specialty>.py` (frozen models per `CONTRIBUTING.md`).
3. Validator: `scripts/validate_<specialty>.py` (release-gate-wired self-test).
4. Runbook: `scripts/<specialty>_sweep.py` OR equivalent paired runbook
   per `akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc` Rule 1.
5. Cursor rule: `.cursor/rules/akos-<specialty>.mdc` (this rule's shape).
6. Skill: `.cursor/skills/<specialty>-craft/SKILL.md` (the *how* layer).
7. SOP+runbook pair: `SOP-<AREA>_<SPECIALTY>_001.md` with AC-HUMAN +
   AC-AUTOMATION acceptance.
8. PEOPLE_DESIGN_PATTERN_REGISTRY.csv row.
9. PRECEDENCE.md canonical + mirror rows.
10. HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md §6 row + linked_canonicals frontmatter +
    forward_charters when applicable.
11. CHANGELOG.md entry.
12. `process_list.csv` row when applicable.
13. `validate_hlk.py` umbrella registration when umbrella-scoped.
14. `config/verification-profiles.json` `pre_commit` step (INFO ramp).
15. `scripts/release-gate.py` advisory wiring.

All 15 surfaces land in the same commit (or the next material commit) so
the specialty is operationally complete before being advertised. This
rule's own mint commit is the worked example.

